<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Rooster (<span class="chinese-char">雞</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>You (酉)</strong>, carrying pure Yin Metal energy. In the 2026 Fire Horse year, the Rooster faces the <strong>overcoming cycle</strong> — Fire melts Metal. As Yin Metal (jewellery, refined objects), the Rooster is more sensitive to Fire's pressure than the Monkey's Yang Metal.</p>
      <p>The year's energy challenges the Rooster's preference for order, precision, and control. Fire's unpredictable, passionate nature disrupts routines and forces adaptation. However, the Rooster's greatest strength — the ability to maintain standards and create order from chaos — becomes <strong>exceptionally valuable</strong> precisely because it's in short supply during a Fire Horse year.</p>
      <p>The Rooster's secret friend is the <strong>Dragon</strong>, which is having an excellent 2026 (Fire generates Dragon's Earth). This alliance provides practical support and opens doors. The Rooster who maintains quality while accepting the year's faster pace achieves meaningful progress.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>Career dynamics in 2026 reward the Rooster's <strong>organisational abilities and critical thinking</strong>. While Fire signs chase bold visions, someone must manage the details, timelines, and quality standards — the Rooster fills this essential role. Recognition may come more slowly than for Fire-aligned signs, but it is more durable.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> faces pressure similar to the Monkey's, as Metal wealth is challenged by Fire. The Rooster should protect savings, avoid speculative investments, and focus on steady income growth through demonstrated expertise. Financial planning and budgeting — the Rooster's natural strengths — are especially important.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Finance, accounting, quality control, auditing, law, healthcare, precision engineering, jewellery, fashion, and any field requiring meticulous attention to detail and high standards.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The Fire-Metal dynamic in romance means <strong>passion meets perfectionism</strong>. The Rooster's critical nature may be amplified under stress, leading to excessive fault-finding in relationships. Conscious effort to express appreciation and soften criticism is essential for relationship harmony.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Roosters</strong> may find the year's romantic energy too chaotic for comfort. Quality over quantity is the guiding principle — one meaningful connection outweighs many superficial ones. The Dragon's secret friend energy means networking through successful, established circles yields the best romantic prospects.</p>
      <p>The <strong>Snake and Ox months</strong> (May and January) provide the San He metal triangle's harmonious energy, creating the most emotionally comfortable periods for relationship development.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>As pure Yin Metal, the Rooster is the zodiac sign <strong>most vulnerable to Fire's health effects</strong> on the Metal organ system. Respiratory health, skin conditions, and large intestine function require careful monitoring. Air quality, allergens, and dietary irritants should be managed proactively.</p>
      <p><strong>Stress management</strong> is critical. The Rooster's tendency to internalise frustration and express it as physical symptoms (skin flare-ups, throat problems, digestive upset) is amplified under Fire pressure. Talk therapy, journaling, and confiding in trusted friends help process emotional stress before it manifests physically.</p>
      <p><strong>Exercise</strong> should emphasise precision and discipline: martial arts forms, ballet, swimming laps (water element), or structured gym routines. The Rooster doesn't enjoy chaotic group activities — solo or one-on-one training maintains motivation and control.</p>
    </section>

